textBeforeTable: Jim Beckmann, Online Content Coordinator Oh, and don’t forget that on December 31st, we’re counting down the Top Albums of 2009, as voted on by you, our listeners, and then on January 4th, we’ll count down the Top Albums of the Decade. Tune in all day! The authors of the lists below consist of full-time employees, part-time staff, DJ assistants, regular interns, NYC volunteers, and a whole lot more — and just as their roles at the station vary, so do their musical tastes. Here, you’ll find the expected, the unanticipated, and the unknown. Coming up soon, we’ll feature their Top Albums of the Decade as well. KEXP DJs have turned in their lists for Top Ten Albums of 2009, but what about the rest of the hardworking staff and volunteers? KEXP is supported by a legion of music-loving people who are dedicated to the mission of sharing musical discovery with everyone else they can.
